odge skills are maxxed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uanguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anguss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 378<br> <font color=#333333>(8/27/02 1:09:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: skill-up</span><hr size=1> Dexterity is the stat which impacts combat skills gains.  Agility provides minimal AC, which is not the same as defense.  Ac is a result of defense.  One thing about combat skills, they generally only will advance when your engaged with dark blues.<br>
<br>
That being said. I tanked quite a bit all the way up, so not sure where would be best.  I would probably get a group up and hit somewhere with blue undead like Howling Stones.  They dont' hit too hard, but will hit the closest person generally.  This allows you to bounce in and out of range and take hits while actually gaining exp/loot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and not putting yerself or party in serious jeapordy. <p>Toem, Arch Mage<br>
