<br>
The rule for skill increases has always been whether or not the mob gives experience, not the color of the con.<br>
<br>
- Lego, 60 Druid<br>
- Dyng, 50 Mage<br>
- Clearmist, 51 Enchanter<br>
- Brouhaha, 51 Warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulegolys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legolys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/02 3:04:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=28>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's up with defense?</span><hr size=1> And AGI buffs *should* help with raising defense.  Think of it this way - You can only get a skill up in defense if a mob misses you.  Agility impacts the *avoidance* portion of your AC, causing you to be missed more.  So Agi buff = More Misses = More chances for a defense skill-up.<br>
<br>
And if your defense skill is low as it stands, you'll need every extra chance for a miss you can get.<br>
<br>
Note that AC buffs such as the Phantom Armor line, Cleric buffs, Enchanter buffs, and others are believed to only impact the *mitigation* portion of AC.  Each time the mob hits you, it will be for less average dmg, but the mob still hits the same number of times.  So these buffs will most likely not help increase your chance for skill-ups. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulegolys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legolys</A> at: 8/29/02 3:05:28 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=314.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=314.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=314.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=28><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.threadControl?topicID=314.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=314.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=314.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum meth